CreateC++Project for MacOS

A simple tool to create C++ project structure on Windows.

Using Compiler C++ for MacOS: Clang

Usage:
1. CreateC++Project in PATH (/usr/local/bin)
2. Open Terminal
3. Run:

   CreateC++Project <name>

This will generate a basic C++ project with source files and build setup.

This tool only creates a basic C++ project structure.
It does NOT replace Make or CMake.

Author: Devdez